<section id="when-not-to">
  <h2>When Not To Use Fluid Scaling</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Pixel-precise dashboards</strong> &mdash; data-dense UIs where every pixel matters may prefer fixed tokens.</li>
    <li><strong>Print stylesheets</strong> &mdash; print media has a fixed page size; fluid scaling adds no value.</li>
    <li><strong>Embedded widgets</strong> &mdash; components that render at a known fixed size don't benefit from viewport-relative scaling. Use container queries instead.</li>
    <li><strong>Existing breakpoint systems</strong> &mdash; if your project already has a mature breakpoint-based approach, mixing in fluid tokens can create unpredictable interactions.</li>
  </ul>
</section>
